title: Rounded college-jerseyesque sans-serif
content:
Hi all,

just wondered if anyone could identify this college-style sans-serif. Thankyou!

 ![](http://web.archive.org/web/20130818175944im_/http:/typophile.com/files/font_3494.jpg)
author: nicholasgross

comments.content: Can't believe I've stumped the typophiles … any ideas? Or maybe it's so obvious it's embarrassing to say? :)
[PIXymbols Far Marks](http://web.archive.org/web/20130818175944/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/pixymbols/far-marks) looks to match for me.
Thanks Ryuk. I think it's close but these letters look a bit bolder and the S terminals are a bit different

Some more (freebies), not even sure they come closer than Far Marks though: [Jefferies](http://web.archive.org/web/20130818175944/http:/www.dafont.com/jefferies-jaynz.font), [Amarillo USAF](http://web.archive.org/web/20130818175944/http:/www.dafont.com/amarillo-usaf.font)
